cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper presents a technique for normalization in deep learning, specifically for computer vision tasks such as detection, segmentation, and video classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the limitations of batch normalization and proposes an alternative method, which involves computing mean and variance within groups of channels. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper presents experimental results on ResNet-50 trained in ImageNet, COCO object detection and segmentation, and Kinetics video classification, indicating that the paper could also be relevant to categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
